{
  "texts": [
    "The biological mechanisms underlying how we perceive smell and taste are distinct, resulting in varied consumer interactions that influence how products are marketed and developed.",
    "The olfactory and gustatory systems each process sensory information through different biological pathways.",
    "Olfactory signals are detected by odorant receptors in the nasal cavity, which activate neural pathways linked to the olfactory bulb and the limbic system-regions associated with emotions and memory.",
    "This powerful connection renders olfaction particularly impactful in evoking feelings and memories, often influencing consumer behavior through advertising and product design.",
    "For instance, Doucé and Janssens (2013) has shown that pleasant scents can enhance the perception of taste, thereby boosting overall enjoyment."
  ]
}